Hi Parent_E—thanks for reaching out, and I’m glad to hear Nursery_C is your first choice.

In general, we evaluate applications primarily by our priority order when we receive [APPLY] messages, and we confirm a place when we send [ACCEPT]. If we have more applicants than available places, we follow that priority order; if there were ever a true tie, we would use a consistent tie-break (e.g., a fair/random or time-based rule) to decide.

If you’d like to strengthen your application, the most helpful thing is simply to apply when you’re ready and clearly confirm that Nursery_C is your top choice and you would accept immediately if offered. If you have any relevant constraints (start date, schedule needs), you can include those as well so we can confirm fit quickly.

If you want, you can send an [APPLY] either this round or next—just note that we may need to review all interest we receive before finalizing an [ACCEPT].
